        HOWTOAPPLYRTI: 'How to File RTI ?',
        HOWTOAPPLYRTITEXT: ' 1).   Identify the Department to which you wish to file the RTI Application. 2). 	Write your queries in the Application. 3).	Whom should the RTI Application be addressed to? 4).	When will the response be provided to your RTI Application? 5).	Pay the Prescribed fee as per Uttarakhand RTI Rules 6).	Submit the Application.',
        HOWDOIKNOWSTATUSOFMYAPPLICATION: 'How to File RTI Application Online at citizen Portal?',
        HOWDOIKNOWSTATUSOFMYAPPLICATIONTEXT: '1) Visit the Citizen Portal page and write your question in simple English. 2) Proceed with the Payment to complete your application. 3) Our Team of D S C L  R T I experts and lawyers will draft your application and will send it to the concerned Public Authority / Department. 4) Upon receiving a response from the concerned Public Authority / Department our team will inform you about the Letter Of Indent. 5) Proceed with the Payment of Letter Of Indent and receive the information requested.',
        HOWTOUPLOADDOC: 'What is the Fee for RTI  and Payment Options ?',
        HOWTOUPLOADDOCTEXT: 'Govt. of Uttarakhand have prescribed the Uttarakhand Right to Information (Regulation of Fee and Cost) Rules, 2005. The application fee is Rs.10/- Fee can be paid by the following way Court Fee/Demand Draft/Bankers Cheque/online/Pay Order to the State Public Information Officer/State Assistant Public Information Officer.',
        WHOCANAPPLY: 'Who can apply for RTI?',
        WHOCANAPPLYTEXT: 'This Web Portal can be used by citizens of india and residents of Uttrakhand to file RTI application online and also to make payment for RTI application online. First appeal can also be filed online.',
        DREQUESTFAQ: 'What all departments can be requested to obtain any information under RTI act ?',
        DREQUESTFAQTEXT: 'An Applicant who desires to obtain any information under the RTI Act can make a request through this Web Portal to the Departments of Municipal Corportation of Dehradun Nagar Nigam.',
        CITIZENPROVERTYFAQ: 'Do Citizen Below Poverty line need to pay for information ?',
        CITIZENPROVERTYFAQTEXT: 'No RTI fee is not required to be paid by any citizen who is below poverty line as per RTI Rules, 2005. However, the applicant must attach a copy of the certificate issued by the appropriate government in this regard, along with the application.',
        RESPONSEPROVIDEFAQ: 'When will the response be provided to my RTI Application?',
        RESPONSEPROVIDEFAQITEM: 'According to the RTI Act, the response to the RTI application in Uttarakhand, or any other state should be provided by the PIO within 30 days from the receipt of the same. This includes applications made online or offline. If the information requested in the RTI relates to another department, then the PIO is mandated to transfer the same within 5 days from the receipt of the RTI to that department who has the information.',
        FIRSTAPPEALFAQ: 'When First Appeal can be submitted ?',
        FIRSTAPPEALFAQTEXT: ' A First Appeal can be filed to the First Appellate Authority (FAA) if there is no response from the government office after completion of 30 days or if the Applicant is not satisfied with the response of RTI Application.',
        SECONDAPPEALFAQ: 'When Second Appeal can be submitted ?',
        SECONDAPPEALFAQTEXT: 'In case you are not satisfied with the outcome of the First Appeal, or there has been no order passed by FAA, A Second Appeal can be filed to Uttarakhand Information Commission.',
        INFORMATIONRULEFAQ: 'Uttarakhand Right to Information Rules - 2013',
        INFORMATIONRULEFAQTEXT: 'Uttarakhand Right to Information Rules - 2013.',
